  "text": "Fear of failure is one of the main psychological and cultural obstacles to new business creation, particularly for young potential entrepreneurs (Seibert and Lumpkin 2010). Starting up a new business is often associated with high levels of risk-taking, as well as with income and job uncertainty, which may generate a substantial amount of anxiety, and therefore, prompt a delay in performing critical behaviors or even impede acting in the long-term [CITATION_1] . Fear of failure is a multidimensional construct, with emotional, cognitive and identity implications: anticipations of failure bring into memory past experiences of shame and embarrassment, and entail the risk of disappointing important others [CITATION_2] .",
